sentences: Jonathan Charles Toogood (born in Wellington, New Zealand, on 9 August 1971) is the frontman (lead vocals and guitar) of the New Zealand rock band Shihad.
He formed the band in 1988 with fellow Wellingtonian Tom Larkin.
In 2009 Toogood revealed he had been travelling around New Zealand to collaborate with other New Zealand artists for a project that is "extra-curricular" to Shihad's music.
"The Adults" was released as a full-length album in New Zealand in June 2011.
In 2020 Toogood was inducted into Massey University's College of Creative Arts' hall of fame.
Toogood is not related to the broadcasting icon Selwyn Toogood, as his parents migrated from England to New Zealand in the 1950s.
As of April 2005, Toogood was married to Ronise Paul, with whom he had a stepdaughter named Anaya.
Toogood married Dana Salih, who is a Sudanese Muslim, in Sudan in 2014.
The Aotearoa Music Awards (previously known as New Zealand Music Awards (NZMA)) are an annual awards night celebrating excellence in New Zealand music and have been presented annually since 1965.
